sections.text:
As used in the Habitat Protection Act:

A. "commission" means the state game commission;

B. "cross-country" means travel over the countryside other than by road;

C. "vehicle" means any motor-powered mechanical device used for conveyance; and

D. "road" means any maintained or unmaintained right-of-way that has been utilized by the public and includes roads, streets, highways and state scenic, recreation or historical trails.

History:1953 Comp., § 53-6-2, enacted by Laws 1973, ch. 242, § 2.

The commission may expend such funds as become available from the game protection fund, state or federal grants or other sources to carry out the provisions of the Habitat Protection Act including, but not limited to:

A. investigations and surveys of actual or possible wildlife habitat damage by vehicles and the study of areas to be recommended for recreational vehicle use;

B. posting notices of restrictions, prohibitions and permitted use of vehicles;

C. providing maps and other necessary information to the public;

D. an informational and educational program on wildlife habitat preservation and restoration; or

E. the enforcement of the provisions of the Habitat Protection Act.

History:1953 Comp., § 53-6-7, enacted by Laws 1973, ch. 242, § 7.
